Dapo Oyebanjo a.k.a D’banj has expressed his gratitude to Nigerians for their support and messages of condolence during the passing of his first son Daniel Oyebanjo III. Daniel drowned on Sunday, June 24 in a swimming pool at the Oyebanjo’s Lagos residence. The entertainer who spoke on behalf of his wife and family took to his Instagram to speak for the first time since the demise of Daniel Jr. “We want to use this medium to thank everyone that has extended a hand of support to us during this period,” he wrote. “On behalf of myself and my family, we are awed by the demonatration of love and care from both near and afar. “May God bless you all. From the Oyebanjos.